@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
INTRODUCTION:

PhotoCdAga_GUI is just an interface for the @{"PhotoCDAGA" link "PhotoCDAGA" 0} program by Gunther
Rohrich available on Aminet in gfx/show/PhotoCDAGA12.lha.

I liked that program very much, but... I hate using shell! So I wrote the
Gui @{"myself" link "Shareware" 0}!


Hope you like it!
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
REQUIREMENTS:

An Amiga with lot of (virtual) memory and:

- AGA chipset

- 68020 or higher processor

- OS 3.0 or higher

- a CD-ROMdrive capable of reading Photo-CD's

- @{"PhotoCDAGA12" link "PhotoCDAGA" 0} by Gunther Rohrich from Aminet (gfx/show)


For the overview (option -0) you need an overview file.
(PHOTO_CD/OVERVIEW.PCD)
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
USAGE:

PhotoCdAga_GUI is very simple and easy, so I won't waste time and words to
explain you the usage. For the instructions, please read the manual of
PhotoCdAGA by Gunther Rohrich available on Aminet in
gfx/show/@{"PhotoCDAGA12.lha" link "PhotoCDAGA" 0}.

To install it, just copy iy wherever you want and copy PhotoCdAGA in c:

Just two words about the file names: Kodak PhotoCDs has the images stored as
"ImgXXXX.PCD" where XXXX is a number from 1 to 100 (the digits are probably
four for future improvements!); now, since some CDs have the images stored
with other names (for example CD of AmigaFormat uses "Image.XXXX.PCD")
there's a string gadget to insert the name of files. The name is without the
XXXX.PCD, so the default value will be just "Img", but you will have to
change to "Image." to use AmigaFormat CDs.
@endnode

